//PART A — Create Web Service (Node.js)//
Step 1 — Open VS Code

Open VS Code

Click File → Open Folder

Create a new folder
Example:

currency-service
Step 2 — Open Terminal in VS Code

Press:

Ctrl + `

or

Terminal → New Terminal
Step 3 — Initialize Node Project

Run this command:

npm init -y

This creates:

package.json
Step 4 — Install Required Packages

Run:

npm install express body-parser

This installs the libraries required for the web service.

Step 5 — Create Server File

Create a new file:

server.js

Paste this code:

const express = require('express');
const bodyParser = require('body-parser');

const app = express();
const port = 3000;

app.use(bodyParser.json());

app.post('/convert', (req, res) => {
 const amountInRs = req.body.amount_in_rs;

 const conversionRate = 0.0145;
 const amountInUsd = amountInRs * conversionRate;

 res.json({ amount_in_usd: amountInUsd });
});

app.listen(port, () => {
 console.log(`Currency conversion service is running at http://localhost:${port}`);
});

This code creates the INR → USD converter API. 

CLOUD COMPUTING AND WEB SERVICE…

Step 6 — Run the Server

In VS Code terminal run:

node server.js

Output:

Currency conversion service is running at http://localhost:3000

//PART B — Test API Using Postman//
Step 7 — Open Postman

Select POST method

Enter URL:

http://localhost:3000/convert
Step 8 — Add Request Body

Go to:

Body → Raw → JSON

Write:

{
 "amount_in_rs": 1000
}

Click Send

Step 9 — Output

You will get:

{
 "amount_in_usd": 14.5
}

Because conversion rate used:

1 INR = 0.0145 USD
//PART C — Run Java Client//

Create file:

JavaClient.java

Paste code:

import java.net.URI;
import java.net.http.HttpClient;
import java.net.http.HttpRequest;
import java.net.http.HttpResponse;

public class JavaClient {
 public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {

 HttpClient client = HttpClient.newHttpClient();

 String apiUrl = "http://localhost:3000/convert";

 String requestBody = "{\"amount_in_rs\": 1000}";

 HttpRequest request = HttpRequest.newBuilder()
 .uri(URI.create(apiUrl))
 .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
 .POST(HttpRequest.BodyPublishers.ofString(requestBody))
 .build();

 HttpResponse<String> response =
 client.send(request, HttpResponse.BodyHandlers.ofString());

 System.out.println("Response Code: " + response.statusCode());
 System.out.println("Response Body: " + response.body());
 }
}
Step 10 — Compile and Run

Run in terminal:

javac JavaClient.java

then

java JavaClient

Output:

Response Code: 200
Response Body: {"amount_in_usd":14.5}